  "description": [
    "friday July 3 1953 Was Jascha Heifetz Justified in Playing German Music In Israel Was Jascha Heifetz justified in defying protests against his play ing objectionable German music in Israel Two editorial comments are of special interest The Reconstructionist comment ed The recent attack by a terror ist fanatic on Jascha Heifetz in Israel indicates that the terror istic impulse once unleashed is difficult to control and subdue To be sure Mr Heifetz need not have played the Richard Strauss piece which occasioned the inci dent He had been warned of possible extremist reaction He knew of the longstanding Israeli attitude towards German music especially that written by Nazi sympathizers and there was no great principle of esthetic integri ty involved But this in no way excuses an act of terrorism The problem of the terrorist is in a BEST WISHES McFARLAN FOOD SHOP Fine Pastries 306 N Main St Phone 6291 HENDERSONVILLE NC BEST WISHES ALWAYS RAMONA D MARTIN DALE Public Stenographer Notary Public 430 North Church Hendersonville N C Office Phone 9635 i BEST WISHES ALWAYS SEE MURPHYS FOR Adding Machines Safes Typewriters SUPPLIES SALES SERVICE 107 4th Ave E in Bank Bldg Dial 6298 HENDERSONVILLE NORTH CAROLINA"
  ],
